flavorText: It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.
With its long fangs, this surprisingly violent Pokémon can gnaw away even thick concrete with ease.
Although it's said to bring disaster, in actuality, this Pokémon possesses a calm disposition and warns people of any crises that loom.
As powerful as an excavator, its ears can reduce dense bedrock to rubble. When it's finished digging, it lounges lazily.
It looks like an aquatic plant and serves as a ferry to Pokémon that can't swim.
Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.
It submerges itself in sand and moves as if swimming. This wise behavior keeps its enemies from finding it and maintains its temperature.
It is small but rough and tough. It won't hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.
It shakes its tail vigorously when it emits ultrasonic waves strong enough to reduce concrete to rubble.
When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity can cause lightning storms.
It prefers hot and humid environments. It is quick at capturing prey with its vines.
Overwhelmed by enigmatic abilities, it suffers a constant headache. It sometimes uses mysterious powers.
Using electricity stored in its fur, it stimulates its muscles to heighten its reaction speed.
Their fur feels so good that if two of them snuggle together, they won't want to be separated.
Feared for its wrath and the curses it spreads, this Pokémon will also, on a whim, cast spells that help people.
Born in the spout of a volcano, its body is covered by flames that shimmer like the sun.
It is said to deliver happiness. Being compassionate, it shares its egg with injured people.
Known as "The Being of Knowledge." It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.
Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.
It sleeps in a deep-sea trench. If it flaps its wings, it is said to cause a 40-day storm.
It wears a rag fashioned into a Pikachu costume in an effort to look less scary. Unfortunately, the costume only makes it creepier.
Its well-developed jaws are powerful and capable of crushing anything. Even its trainer must be careful.
Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females' flying abilities surpass those of the males.
It has an easygoing nature. It doesn't care if it bumps its head on boats and boulders while swimming.
Its newly grown legs prevent it from running. It appears to prefer swimming over trying to stand.
They move in groups of a few individuals. A female is often the leader of the group, and the males will gather food.
A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.
It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain.
Using its tail as a float, it dives underwater. It likes eating plants that grow on river bottoms.
They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves against Heatmor.
The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.
No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokémon, it will silence you violently.
Their beautiful form comes from the muscles they have developed. They run silently in the night.
It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.
It eats its weight in leaves every day. It fends off attackers with the needle on its head.
The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.
It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.
Their cute act is a ruse. They trick people and steal their valuables just to see the looks on their faces.
The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.
Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.
For some reason, it likes to land on people's heads softly and act like it's a hat.
Each follows its Trainer's orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.
It is believed that the variety of types of this Pokémon were created by evolutionary adaptation, as each possesses a different ability.
Stiffens its ears to sense danger. The larger, more powerful of its horns secretes venom.
It attacks using its huge mouth. While its attacks are powerful, it hurts itself out of clumsiness, too.
Ancient people believed that petitioning Bronzong for rain was the way to make crops grow.
This Pokémon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.
It has a cunning yet savage disposition. It waits for parents to leave their nests, and then it sneaks in to steal their eggs.
It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokémon obey it.
Its six eggs converse using telepathy. They can quickly gather if they become separated.
Its movements are powered by a mysterious energy. It has continued to move since ancient times, so its power may soon run out.
Their fur feels so good that if two of them snuggle together, they won't want to be separated.
The ultrasonic waves it generates by rubbing its two wings together cause severe headaches.
The world's first artificially created Pokémon. It can travel through electronic space.
This Pokémon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it's believed that Sableye will steal people's spirits away.
It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago
Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.
It uses its tail to absorb electricity from power plants or from outlets in houses, and then it fires the electricity from its whiskers.
The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny spikes, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.
Its unique faculty of sight can detect small prey more than 30 miles away, even in the midst of a sandstorm.
Some say that ancient people invented Golurk to serve as a laborer. It follows its master's orders faithfully.
On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.
Its fluffy coat swells to double when static electricity builds up. Touching it can be shocking.
This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.
Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.
They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.
If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.
From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.
When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.
Proud of its sturdy skull, it suddenly headbutts everything, but its weight makes it unstable, too.
Many people believe that, deep in the forest where Tranquill live, there is a peaceful place where there is no war.
It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.
It flies gracefully through the sky. Its melodic humming makes you feel like you're in a dream.
It discharges positive and negative electricity from its antenna tips to shock its foes.
It changes so it looks like its foe, tricks it, and then uses that opportunity to flee.
Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.
To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.
Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.
Known as "The Being of Emotion." It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.
It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.
It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.
It hides itself by kicking up desert sand with its wings. Red covers shield its eyes from sand.
To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.
As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, though colored black.
Because its genetic makeup is irregular, it quickly changes its form due to a variety of causes.
Its head sports an altered form of whiskers made of metal. When in communication with its comrades, its whiskers wobble to and fro.
Loving to battle, this Pokémon pinches all Pokémon that enter its territory with its pincers and throws them out.
It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.
This Pokémon lives in cold water. It leaves the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.
They travel in groups of four or five, leaving signs for one another on trees and rocks. They bring down their prey with coordinated attacks.
Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.
It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokémon obey it.
Although slow, it is skilled at fishing with its tail. It does not feel pain if its tail is bitten.
Emanations from its fingertips solidify the air into invisible walls that repel even harsh attacks.
After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.
It looks just like a Poké Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on touch.
It confuses its enemies by flying too quickly for the eye to follow. It has a hair-trigger temper but forgets what made it angry an instant later.
It radiates such a powerful magnetic field that nearby electrical appliances become unusable.
It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.
It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.
It chews its way through boulders with its sturdy jaws. Its eyes can see in the darkness underground.
Recognizing their own weakness, they always live in a group. When alone, a Staravia cries noisily.
Their beautiful form comes from the muscles they have developed. They run silently in the night.

It vanishes into seaweed and remains perfectly still to avoid attacks from large Pokémon. Rotten seaweed is its main food source.
The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.
Its shining gold hair provides it with protection. It's reputed that keeping any of its fallen hairs will bring bad luck.
Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.
While it sleeps, the head of its tail keeps watch. The tail doesn't need to sleep.
This vicious Pokémon sprays a poisonous liquid on opponents that come near. For whatever reason, it gets along really well with Dhelmise.
It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.
It discharges positive and negative electricity from its antenna tips to shock its foes.
When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind's embrace with an untroubled heart.
It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.
It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.
They will challenge anything, even strong opponents, without fear. Their frequent fights help them become stronger.
It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.
It is said to live in another world. The intense light it radiates from the surface of its body can make the darkest of nights light up like midday.
Its massive bones are 1,000 times harder than human bones. It can easily knock a trailer flying.
It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.
It slips into the shadows of others and mimics their powers and movements. As it improves, it becomes stronger than those it's imitating.
It possesses a type of radar, which it can use to find the insects it eats for food, even in pitch darkness.
It looks just like a Poké Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on touch.
They tend to guard their posteriors with suitable bones they have found. They pursue weak Pokémon.
The moonlight that it stores in the wings on its back apparently gives it the ability to float in midair.
By imitating the voice of a child, it causes people to get hopelessly lost deep in the forest. It's trying to make friends with them.
This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.
It chases people and Pokémon from its territory by causing them to experience deep, nightmarish slumbers.
A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.
Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving, its body will cool and harden.
